	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Well, I redid the mod completely. At the same time I modded to other PAL Sneses.
<br />
<br />Both the PAL snes' now swap 50/60Hz perfectly, and still the jap snes will not shift from 60Hz. At all. Its rock solid. I used new switches, a different resistor (in fact one pulled from a another working mode). Bleeped out all the connections once soldered. 
<br />
<br />I can only guess more human error. 
<br />
<br />I notice this is an extremely old jap snes - it is a plug-in sound module in silver casing at the back that physically detaches from the motherboard, which I believe means its one of the earlier snes models.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
